1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
Most business AI tells an owner how to grow.
Risk Sovereignty asks a harder question:
when the world stops cooperating, what breaks first—
and which move preserves the right to choose again tomorrow?

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:35,000
This company appears profitable before stress.
But delayed collections, a partial debt call, and inventory impairment
consume more cash than it holds.
The first failure is cash—the weakest constraint.

3
00:00:35,000 --> 00:01:05,000
The numbers are not generated by AI.
Business facts and stress assumptions stay visible and editable.
A deterministic engine recalculates cash flow, shock, runway,
and five lifelines in real time.

4
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Risk Sovereignty avoids the false choice
between doing nothing and shutting down.
It verifies that the exit is real, removes exposure in stages,
and preserves resources to participate again.

5
00:01:30,000 --> 00:02:15,000
GPT-5.6 is not allowed to invent financial truth.
The server forces a strict function call to the stress-test engine.
The submitted case is calculated locally and returned to the model.
A second pass completes the sovereignty gate before staged actions.

6
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Every action cites calculation or assumption evidence.
A local method audit rejects imaginary evidence or broken phase order.
The interface separates user facts, editable assumptions,
deterministic calculations, and AI judgment.
The audit strip proves a live run.

7
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Risk Sovereignty does not predict the future.
It controls exposure, preserves exit rights,
and helps a small-business owner keep the next move.
